<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00157</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT ESTABLISHING A RENTAL SUBSIDY PROGRAM FOR INFORMAL SETTLER FAMILIES (ISFS) AND APPROPRIATING FUNDS THEREFOR</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Establishes a housing and social protection program for the ISFs to lead decent lives and access to the formal housing market .

Provides flat-rate rental subsidy to eligible low-income ISFs to rent accommodation in the private rental market for a maximum of five (5) years or upon availment of permanent housing, whichever comes first.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : “Rental Subsidy Program for ISFs Act.”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>BELMONTE, JOSE CHRISTOPHER Y.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-07-01</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Tambunting (000 2019-08-28)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON HOUSING AND URBAN DEVELOPMENT ON 2019-07-23</td></tr></table>